The experts at the international conference in which our association was involved were not very satisfied that we have voluntary vaccination.
That's not ideal.
On the other hand, we are glad that we have managed to achieve at least that.
I think that's the way we have to go now, Kalovsky led.
However, the Ministry of Health does not intend to change the vaccination procedure against pneumococcal disease.
At this moment we are not considering this at all, his spokesman Vlastimil Sesen said.
Voluntary vaccination has its disadvantages, the doctors claim.
Hana Cabrnochova, chairman of the specialist company of practical paediatrics, admits that voluntary vaccination has its disadvantages.
