Workshop cost estimate in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in only four steps:Identification of the vehicle, Search for the spare part, Creation and Creation of a cost estimate.
The easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially in order to convince older professionals who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger vehicles, 109 land vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 small transporters and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by means of the chassis number, a graph of the respective model appears and the required spare part is then selected.
The user can include variables such as the price for hours worked, surcharges or discounts, and thereafter he can print out the cost estimate and pass it on to his customers.
AudaTaller, however, is not a tool to evaluate like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
